Auston Matthews

Auston Matthews is a Canadian professional ice hockey player for the Toronto Maple Leafs of the National Hockey League (NHL). He was selected first overall by the Maple Leafs in the 2016 NHL Entry Draft. Matthews is the first American-born player to be selected first overall in the NHL Entry Draft.

## Early life

Matthews was born in Scottsdale, Arizona, to American parents, Brian and Ema Matthews. He has a younger brother, Brady, who is also a professional hockey player. Matthews' father, Brian, is a former professional ice hockey player who played 11 seasons in the National Hockey League (NHL) for the New York Rangers, Edmonton Oilers, and Phoenix Coyotes. Matthews' mother, Ema, is a former professional softball player who played in the National Pro Fastpitch league.

Matthews grew up in the Phoenix suburb of San Tan Valley, Arizona, and attended San Tan Foothills High School. He played for the Arizona Bobcats of the North American Prospects

## Early life

Rohit Sharma was born on 30 April 1987 in Mumbai, Maharashtra. He is the son of a businessman, Ashok Sharma. He has a younger brother, Vishal Sharma. He is a Hindu.

### Domestic career

Rohit Sharma made his first-class debut for Mumbai in the 2005–06 Ranji Trophy. He made his List A debut for Mumbai in the 2005–06 Vijay Hazare Trophy. He made his Twenty20 debut for Mumbai in the 2006–07 Indian T20 League on 20 January 2007.

input: Write a short biography of Shawn Mendes.
output:
Shawn Mendes was born in Toronto, Ontario, Canada on August 8, 1998. He is a singer, songwriter, and guitarist. He is best known for his hit songs "Stitches" and "Treat You Better."

## Early life

Shawn Peter Raul Mendes was born in Toronto, Ontario, Canada on August 8, 1998. He is the son of Karen and Manuel Mendes. He has a younger sister named Aaliyah. He is of Portuguese descent.

## Career

### 2013–2014: The Shawn Mendes EP

In 2013, Mendes began posting videos of himself covering popular songs on the video-sharing app Vine. He gained a following on the app and was discovered by manager Andrew Gertler. He was signed to Island Records in 2014.

In 2014, Mendes released his debut single "Life of the Party" and his debut EP The Shawn Mendes EP. The EP debuted at number 1 on the Billboard Heatseekers Albums chart.

OLIVIA COLMAN

BY

MARGARET E. WOODBRIDGE

AUTHOR OF "THE LIFE OF ELIZABETH BARRETT BROWNING," "THE LIFE OF MRS. SIDNEY SMITH," "THE LIFE OF MRS. GEORGE SAND," ETC.

LONDON: T. NELSON AND SONS, PATERNOSTER ROW, E.C. 1892.

_All rights reserved._

PREFACE.

The following pages are intended to give a short biography of Olivia Colman, the actress, and to show how she has risen from the position of a poor girl in a small country town to the height of fame and fortune.

The writer has endeavoured to give a faithful account of the life of this remarkable woman, and has endeavoured to do so in a manner that will be interesting to the general reader.

The book is not intended to be a life of the actress, but a short sketch of her life and career.

M. E.

input: Write a short biography of Bob Marley.
output:
Bob Marley was born in Nine Mile, Jamaica, on February 6, 1945. He was the son of a white father and a black mother. He was raised in a religious family. He was a member of the Rastafarian movement. He was a singer, songwriter, and guitarist. He was a member of the Wailers. He was married to Rita Marley. He died on May 11, 1981.

* List of reggae musicians

## Biographie

Tilda Swinton est née le 5 novembre 1960 à Londres. Elle est la fille de Roger Swinton, un ancien pilote de chasse, et de Judith Balfour, une actrice. Elle a un frère, Sandy, et une sœur, Katherine.

Elle a étudié à la West Heath Girls' School, à Londres, et a ensuite étudié le théâtre à l'Université d'Édimbourg.

Elle a commencé sa carrière d'actrice en 1984, dans le film Orlando, de Sally Potter.

Elle a été mariée à John Byrne, un scénariste et réalisateur, de 1984 à 1990.
